{block overview-headline}What is Claris FileMaker?{/block}
{block overview}
    <h2><strong>{include overview-headline}</strong></h2>
    <p>
        Claris FileMaker is an <strong>intuitive software</strong> for <strong>creating custom database applications</strong>. It enables businesses and individuals
        to <strong>easily manage data</strong>, <strong>automate processes</strong>, and <strong>develop clear </strong>and structured <strong>applications</strong>
        for desktops, mobile devices, and the web.
    </p>
    <p>
        With user-friendly controls and pre-built templates, you can quickly design a tailored system—for example, for <strong>customer records</strong>,
        <strong>project management</strong>, or <strong>order tracking</strong>,<strong> </strong>or anything else. FileMaker integrates various database
        sources and provides robust data management tools, <strong>simplifying business process organization</strong> and <strong>digitalization</strong>.
    </p>
{/block}

{block key_features-headline}Key Features of the FileMaker Platform{/block}
{block key_features}
    <h2>{include key_features-headline}</h2>
    <ol class="spacing">
        <li><strong>Visual Application Development:</strong> Create application user interfaces quickly and intuitively using a drag-and-drop interface.</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-Platform:</strong> Applications built on this platform work on macOS, Windows, iOS, and the web.</li>
        <li><strong>Integration Capabilities:</strong> FileMaker can be easily integrated with other systems, allowing created applications to connect with external databases or third-party systems via REST API, ODBC/JDBC, or XML.</li>
        <li><strong>Security: </strong>The platform provides robust security features, including data encryption in transit and at rest, role-based access control, and audit logs—essential for enterprise deployment.</li>
        <li><strong>Flexibility: </strong>FileMaker is highly flexible, enabling the development of custom applications for a wide range of use cases, such as CRM and ERP systems, project management, inventory tracking, client management, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Strong Community Support:</strong> FileMaker has an active community of users and developers who share their knowledge and provide support, so you are never alone.</li>
    </ol>
{/block}

{block filemaker_universal-headline}Universal and Adaptable{/block}
{block filemaker_universal}
    <h2>{include filemaker_universal-headline}</h2>
    <p>
        FileMaker <strong>runs on Windows, macOS, iOS, iPadOS</strong>, and even in a <strong>web browser</strong>.
        This means you can use it in the <strong>environment</strong> you are <strong>familiar</strong> with and
        that <strong>suits your needs</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Applications built with FileMaker can be <strong>tailored to your specific processes</strong>. This ensures
        that your entire business operates in perfect sync while allowing each team member to focus efficiently and comfortably
        on their tasks. <strong>As a result, work of every individual becomes more productive and enjoyable.</strong>
    </p>
{/block}

{block why_we_use_filemaker-headline}Why We at 24U Love Using Claris FileMaker{/block}
{block why_we_use_filemaker}
    <h2>{include why_we_use_filemaker-headline}</h2>
    <p>
        At 24U, we use Claris FileMaker because <strong>it allows us to quickly and efficiently develop smart applications tailored precisely
            to our customers' needs</strong>. Thanks to its flexibility, we can easily <strong>automate processes</strong>, integrate various
        data sources, and <strong>simplify daily work</strong>. With fast and efficient development, FileMaker helps us <strong>respond
            quickly to changing needs</strong>, save time, and deliver<strong> innovative solutions</strong> that streamline business management
        and improve our customers' productivity.
    </p>
    <p>
        FileMaker has been a <strong>successful platform</strong> since 1984, and <strong>backed by Apple</strong> since 1987.
        At <strong>24U</strong>, we have been <strong>working with it for decades</strong> — some of us since 1991 — and over time we've
        seen many proofs that with just a <strong>short learning curve</strong>, <strong>anyone can use it effectively</strong> to optimize
        and accelerate business processes.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you’re not familiar with FileMaker yet, <strong>don’t hesitate</strong> to take the first step—<strong>discover this powerful software</strong>
        and unlock its potential.
    </p>
{/block}

{block why_filemaker_suits_customers-headline}Why FileMaker Suits Our Customers{/block}
{block why_filemaker_suits_customers}
    <h2>{include why_filemaker_suits_customers-headline}</h2>
    <p>
        Using the Claris FileMaker software platform brings businesses <strong>greater efficiency</strong>, <strong>time savings</strong>, and
        <strong>better work organization</strong>. It allows users <strong>to work with data intuitively</strong>, <strong>automate repetitive tasks</strong>, and
        <strong>create clear custom applications</strong> without the need for complex programming.
    </p>
    <p>
        With its ability to be quickly adjusted, <strong>FileMaker can adapt to business growth and evolving needs</strong>. This enables companies
        to <strong>tailor their software to what sets them apart from the competition</strong>, rather than being forced to conform to how the
        software is designed.
    </p>
{/block}

{block where_filemaker_is_used-headline}Where FileMaker Is Used{/block}
{block where_filemaker_is_used}
    <h2>{include where_filemaker_is_used-headline}</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>Thanks to its versatility, intuitiveness, and ease of customization, Claris FileMaker is used across virtually all industries—especially 
        where people want to approach things differently, innovatively, more efficiently, and effectively:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul class="spacing">
        <li>
            <strong>Small and Medium-Sized Businesses: </strong>Companies use FileMaker to create custom applications tailored to their specific needs,
            such as customer management, order tracking, inventory management, or specialized processes.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Large Enterprises: </strong>In corporate environments, high security standards, web accessibility, and seamless integration with
            other systems make FileMaker a valuable tool.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Educational Institutions: </strong>Schools and universities frequently use FileMaker to manage student information, class records,
            and other educational resources. Its intuitive user interface makes it easy for anyone to learn and use quickly.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Nonprofit Organizations:</strong> FileMaker enables nonprofits to build custom applications without requiring large software
            development investments. The applications can also be easily adapted for users with accessibility needs.
        </li>
    </ul>
{/block}

{block what_is_new-headline}What's New in the Current Version{/block}
{block what_is_new}
    <h2>{include what_is_new-headline}</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>FileMaker 2025</strong> is here, and it's a game changer. With <strong>AI</strong> now <strong>fully integrated</strong> across <strong>Pro, Go, Server, WebDirect</strong>, and <strong>APIs</strong>, your data isn't just organised, it's <strong>intelligent</strong>. Build <strong>smarter apps faster, automate like never before</strong>, and tap into <strong>lightning-fast JSON</strong> (up to 15× speed boost). Seamless <strong>Claris Studio</strong> and <strong>Connect</strong> integration means you're ready for the future today. <strong>You’ve got the data</strong>. Now let AI do the heavy lifting. <strong>Upgrade to FileMaker 2025</strong> and lead the smart revolution.
    </p>
    <p>
        Last year brought <strong>semantic search, text summarization</strong>, and <strong>text-based application control</strong>. In <strong>2025</strong>, these foundations evolve into a robust, fully integrated AI toolkit - ready for you to <strong>build smarter, faster</strong>, and <strong>more intuitive solutions.</strong>
    </p>
{/block}

